{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771769292,"nonce":"qOqjFYY/k9+JLBlDsgmTN2zyGQw=","title":"Accessibility audit: ARIA labels, semantic HTML, screen reader support","message":"The application has almost no accessibility support:\n\n- Only 3 aria-label attributes (all from Bootstrap components)\n- Zero alt attributes on images\n- Zero visually-hidden / sr-only text\n- Icon-only links (edit pencil, add-to-cart, etc.) have no accessible names\n- Form labels may not be properly associated\n- Color is used as the sole indicator for some states (text-danger for unchecked fields)\n- No skip-to-content links\n- Navigation landmarks may be missing\n\nNeeds a full audit and remediation pass. Consider:\n1. Adding aria-labels to all icon-only links and buttons\n2. Proper alt text for any images\n3. Semantic HTML (nav, main, aside landmarks)\n4. Ensuring color is not the only way to convey information\n5. Skip-to-content link\n6. Form label associations\n7. Focus management for modals and turbo navigation","files":null}]}